The paper deals with identifying interesting tweets for users, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category. The paper also uses NLP techniques to analyze the content of tweets, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another possible category. The paper also involves analyzing the network influence of the author and sender, which suggests cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category. The paper also involves analyzing the similarity of tweets, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves training a classifier, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
